(‘SayIt’) Say It: English Pronunciation Privacy Policy and Terms and Conditions
Background
Phona Ltd (a UK registered company, number 08913278) designed and built the Say It: English Pronunciation (‘SayIt’) apps as Freemium apps. They are provided by Phona for English language learners and educators to download at no cost and are intended for use by consumers, as free apps with accessible in-app purchase subscription options.
SayIt offers a 1-month, 3-month or 12-month subscription for access to premium content and features; we are constantly considering improvements and periodically add more content and new features. You can cancel your subscription any time through your App Store or Google Play account. Customers who purchased SayIt version 2 before 2021 will have a period of free access to the premium content on updating to version 3 (subscription) for 12 months. Please contact us at info@phona.co.uk if you need support with this.
Subscriptions
The SayIt app offers a number of different subscription options, on an auto-renewing basis. When you subscribe for the first time, we may offer a free 7-day trial for you to explore all the features of the app and the full 70,000-word dictionary of recordings/words (British and American English accents). After 7 days, if you choose to continue to use the full version of SayIt, your subscription charges will begin.
You can check your renewal date in the Premium tab of the app, and cancel your subscription at any time through your App Store or Google Play account.
In Google Play, we offer an Introductory Price of up to -50% on the first month of a 1-month subscription. Please be aware that after the first month, the cost will revert to the full monthly subscription price.
For more information about managing or cancelling your subscription, see guidelines on the
App Store
or
Google Play
. Alternatively, contact us for support.
If you choose to use SayIt, then you agree to the collection and use of information in relation to this policy, and to our Terms and Conditions below.
Privacy Policy
Information Collection and Use
The Personal Information that we collect is used to improve the app. We will not use or share your information with anyone except as described in this Privacy Policy and Terms and Conditions.
For a better experience while using our apps, we may require you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information. The information that we request will be retained by us and used as described in this Privacy Policy.
The app does use third party services that may collect information used to identify you and provide a better experience.
Google Play Services
Firebase Analytics
App Store Connect
Log Data
Whenever you use SayIt, we may collect log data and information (through third party products). These data may include information such as your device's IP address, device name, operating system version, the configuration of the app when using it, the time and date of your use of the app, and other statistics. These data helps us improve the app functions.
Cookies
Cookies are files with a small amount of data that are commonly used as anonymous unique identifiers. These are sent to your browser from the websites that you visit and are stored on your device's internal memory.
SayIt does not use cookies directly. However, the app may use third party code and libraries that in turn use cookies to collect information and improve their services. You have the option to either accept or refuse these cookies and know when a cookie is being sent to your device. If you choose to refuse cookies, you may not be able to use some portions of this service.
Subscriptions
The SayIt app offers a number of different subscription options, on an auto-renewing basis. You can check your renewal date at any time in the app, and cancel at any time through your app store.
For more information about managing or cancelling your subscription, see guidelines on the
