The app itself, and all the trademarks, copyright, database rights and other intellectual property rights related to it belong to Phona Ltd and its parent company, ProSpeech Technologies Ltd.
Phona is committed to ensuring that the app is as useful and efficient as possible. For that reason, we reserve the right to make changes to the app or to charge for its services, at any time and for any reason. We will never charge you for the app or its services without making it very clear to you exactly what you’re paying for.
The SayIt app stores and processes personal data that you have provided to us, in order to provide our Service. It is your responsibility to keep your phone and access to the app secure.
We strongly recommend that you do not "jailbreak" or "root" your phone: these are the iOs and Android terms for removing software restrictions and limitations imposed by the official operating system of your device. Doing either could make your phone vulnerable to malware or viruses, compromise your phone’s security features and prevent the SayIt app from working properly or at all. Obviously we will bear no responsibility for any losses you incur in these circumstances, and in using the SayIt app you agree to this.
